            "body": "How is this different than multicursor? (Existing ticket)\r\n\r\n> decoupling code in a codebase is good in general, especially when talking about links between internal behavior and the UI-\r\n\r\nCursor in this context is not UI. It is the basic unit of work in the entire system. \"Decoupling\" is therefore a non sequitur.",
