            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "As far as I’m aware, multiple cursors do nothing more or less than echoing each other, then going away. An expanded cursor could have various useful properties, like continued existence in an inactive state, or ownership by 3rd-party implemented functionality, or transformed output, or simply as a change-tracking buffer location for easier scripted buffer manipulation.\r\n\r\nOr maybe I’m grossly incorrect about the capabilities implied when saying “multiple cursors”.\r\n\r\nI’d mostly want this for the plugin possibilities. User-facing multiple cursors would naturally fall out of this change. Perhaps an easier thing to implement that would accomplish most of the same things would be invisible markers, but full “cursorship” would pull in a lot of functionality that would likely be desired for such markers.",
